      "file_path": "cps-rest/src/main/java/org/onap/cps/rest/utils/MultipartFileUtil.java",
      "patchset_number": 6,
      "line": 106,
      "message": "in a context of zip, the folder is just a descriptors indicated by a flag zipEntry.isDirectory() \nand a path of course\nthe file belonging to particular folder is indicated by file's path -> zipEntry.getName()\nall the archives in test resources contain files within folders, \nso this case is already being handled.\nusing folders to organize files should not be a stopper on resource extraction\n\ncurrent (implemented) case is the most simple one: we extract any yang file we find, \nthen try to process them together.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7362,
        "name": "Ruslan Kashapov",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "ruslan.kashapov@pantheon.tech",
        "username": "rkashapov"
